    "Melani et al. [77] explore the use of probabilistic models to address unpredictabilities and dynamics in realistic real-time systems.",
    "They apply statistical analysis to study how various dependences within the system affect task execution times.",
    "Their method involves collecting execution time profiles (ETPs) through extensive measurements, representing these times as probability distributions.",
    "They then analyze these distributions to understand the impact of system events, such as cache effects and scheduling policies, on execution times.",
    "By modeling the dependencies between tasks and system events, they aim to reduce the pessimism of traditional WCET estimates, providing more accurate probabilistic WCET bounds without the need for complex hardware models.Ensuring the set of execution time observations represents all possible execution scenarios is crucial for MBPTA validity."
